ssignment 12 – Service Layer and REST API Development

Overview
This assignment focused on extending the Smart Student Assignment Tracker system by implementing:

- A Service Layer for business logic
- RESTful API endpoints using FastAPI
- Repository abstraction for data access
- OpenAPI/Swagger API documentation
- Unit and integration testing

The implementation follows layered software architecture principles to ensure separation of concerns, maintainability, and scalability.

Implemented Features
Service Layer
The service layer handles business rules and validation logic.

Implemented services:
- AssignmentService

Responsibilities:
- Create assignments
- Retrieve assignments
- Validate assignment data
- Communicate with repository layer

REST API
RESTful endpoints were implemented using FastAPI.

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|--------|-----------|-------------|
| GET | / | API status endpoint |
| GET | /assignments | Retrieve all assignments |
| POST | /assignments | Create a new assignment |

API Documentation
FastAPI automatically generates Swagger/OpenAPI documentation.

Swagger UI:
http://127.0.0.1:8000/docs

Testing
The project includes:
- Unit tests
- Repository tests
- API integration tests
- Coverage reporting

